<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747167>
    dc:description "Figure 11. (a,b) Floridina antiqua (Smitt); NHMUK 1964.7.2.56pt; Recent, Ghana; (a) bleached fragment showing autozooids and two avicularia; all of the autozooids in view are ovicellate apart from the one in the upper left; (b) unbleached fragment with two avicularia. (c,d) Floridina regularis Canu and Bassler; NHMUK D34391; Miocene, Duplin Formation, Cape Fear River, North Carolina, USA; (c) non-ovicellate autozooids; (d) ovicellate autozooids. Scale bars = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4747167/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

